==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trimethylene
<hw>Tri*meth"yl*ene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A gaseous hydrocarbon, <chform>C3H6</chform>, isomeric with
propylene and obtained from it indirectly. It is the base of a series of
compounds analogous to the aromatic hydrocarbons.</def><-- usu. called
cyclopropane, because the three carbons form a ring:⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p> CH2 / \ H2C---CH2 -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trimetric</ent>⟦br⟧
